{#
Optional page-level head include for an extension (legacy Jinja2 / Markdown pipeline).

NOTE: This file is for the legacy Jinja2 → Markdown rendering path only.
In the Astro site (astro/), per-extension styling belongs in a dedicated Astro
component under astro/src/components/. See SectionBlock.astro for how extension
keys dispatch to the right component.

What this file is for (legacy path):
- Add CSS or JS that should only load when this extension section is present
- Add third-party assets such as KaTeX, charts, syntax highlighting, etc.
- Keep extension-specific page tweaks out of the shared site template

How it is used (legacy path):
- templates/daily.md.j2 includes this file once for each rendered section:
    {% include "extensions/" + sec.key + "/head.html.j2" ignore missing %}
- Common render context values:
    sec, date, generated_at, meta, sections_ordered

Safe default:
- Delete this file if your extension does not need extra head assets.
- If building for the Astro site, create an Astro component instead.

Minimal example:
  <style>
    .my-source-card { border-left: 4px solid #1565c0; }
  </style>

  <script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    console.log("my_source assets loaded");
  });
  </script>
#}
